#LinuxTip #Automation #Linux

You can use $timeout command in linux to exit the bash command if it doesn't finishes in time X 

Example: 

$timeout 2 cat *.txt 

If $cat commane doesn't finishes in 2 seconds it will kill the command. Usefull while automation.
